title: Grateful Dead Live at Frost Amphitheatre on 1986-05-11
description:
Set 1

Gimme Some Lovin'-> Dancin' In The Streets, Good Time Blues, Iko Iko, My Brother Esau, It Must Have Been The Roses, Cassidy-> Might As Well

Set 2

Samson & Delilah-> Crazy Fingers-> He's Gone-> Smokestack Lightning-> Drums-> The Other One-> Comes A Time-> Around & Around-> Not Fade Away, E:I Need A Miracle-> E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Nice sound I have never heard a bad Frost recording. This one sounds good to me.Always loved it here the smells in the air around this place are so clean and sweet. The set list is very very good. Love the opener and Crazy Fingers He's Gone Smokestack.
One of the fun things about being in Palo Alto was the shows were early afternoon and that left the rest of the afternoon and evening for a lot of fun.We would usually hit the Buffet at Sizzler steak house after the shows.Good Salad bar and then back to the hotels for an evening of partying. Oh to go back in time and enjoy these shows everyone of them  82 '83 '85 '86 '87' 88' 89.... They loved playing here and we knew it.
